Description: Copper alloy arrow-head, square section with tang.
Curator's comments: Baitinger suggests this arrow-head type was used fromthe mid-6th to the 4th centuries BC (Baitinger 2001, Vierkantige Dornpfeilspitzen types 1B). Baitinger, H. 2001, Die Angriffswaffen aus Olympia, Berlin & New York.
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.69, p.70, p.183, pl.25)
